title: Zapier Sub-zap are Super Powerful - How and When to Use Them
description:
Zapier sub zap - How to set them up. 
Two use cases. 
Use case 1: You find yourself making the same "Find" step in the middle of many zaps - you can create a sub-zap that does the "Find" action and then pulls the info back to the zaps you're working on.  

Use case 2: You find yourself making the same multi-step end to zaps over and over.  You can create many zaps with just the trigger and then have that trigger the one sub-zap that runs the action.

title: What Is Zapier And How Does It Work? (2025)
description:
Zapier is a web-based automation tool that allows users to connect their favorite apps and automate repetitive tasks without any coding knowledge. It works by creating "Zaps," which are automated workflows that connect apps together. Users can choose from over 2,000 apps to create Zaps that trigger actions in one app based on events in another. 

For example, a user can create a Zap that automatically saves Gmail attachments to Dropbox or sends a Slack message when a new task is added in Trello.
